  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001105.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Enlil of the E-adda , En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , given strength by Enlil , nourished on rich milk by Ninhursaĝa , ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001105.11",
      "line_range": "11",
      "translation": "(i 1') ( When ... ) took him by the hand from among the multitude of people , and Enlil granted to En-metena the lofty scepter of destiny from Nibru , ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001105.20",
      "line_range": "20",
      "translation": "(ii 1') ..., he transported ( this ) lofty vase from the mountains for his father , Enlil ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001105.24",
      "line_range": "24",
      "translation": "(ii 5') Šul-MUŠxPA , the personal god of En-metena , ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001105.27",
      "line_range": "27",
      "translation": "(ii 1'') ... by Enlil , fashioned it and dešorated it with purified silver for him ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001105.30",
      "line_range": "30",
      "translation": "(ii 4'') ... this ( vessel ) for his own well-being , for the well-being of Lagaš , and for the well-being of ...."
    }
  ],
